Cape Town â€“ Two people were killed and three others left injured on Sunday night after a four-vehicle collision on the R300 in Kuilsrivier in the Western Cape, ER24 paramedics said on Monday. "ER24 paramedics, along with Life Healthcare, Metro and Fire Services, arrived on the scene to that four vehicles had collided," spokesperson Russel Meiring said. "Local authorities began to close off the road while paramedics inspected the situation. "Upon closer inspection, paramedics found that five people lay trapped inside one of the vehicles. "Upon assessment, paramedics found that one man and a woman had sustained fatal injuries. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the patients and they were declared dead on the scene. "Three other patients were found trapped in the vehicle. One man was found in a critical condition while another man and a woman were found to have sustained moderate injuries. "Rescue and Fire services had to use specialised rescue equipment to free the patients from the vehicle. Once freed, paramedics treated the patients and provided the critically injured man with advanced life support interventions. "The patients were thereafter transported to Tygerberg Hospital for further treatment. The occupants from the other three vehicles fortunately escaped injury. "Local authorities were on scene for further investigations," he said.